    "comment": "Rationale: Figure 10: \"ASAP1, an Arf4 GAP, inhibits dendritic spine formation, and both Arf4-WT and Arf4-Q71L partially rescue this inhibition.\"\n\n20/01/2021 Dnyanada: ASAP1 is a regulator of the actin cytoskeleton (PMID: 10725410). Overexpression of ASAP1-Flag shows a significant decrease in total spine density which is rescued by overexpression of Arf4 indicating that Arf4 and ASAP1 might interact to influence spine cytoskeletal dynamics.. Experimental description: - \"Mixed hippocampal and cortical neuron cultures were prepared from E18-19 mice...\"\n- Species of Flag-tagged ASAP1 is not stated: \"Flag-tagged murine ASAP1 cDNA, a gift from Paul Randazzo (National Cancer Institute, Bethesda, MD), was expressed in the pCR2.1 vector [39]...\" Authors were contacted (dd 22/2/2018 Pim, yhuang@gladstone.ucsf.edu, randazzp@mail.nih.gov)",
